WEBVTT

00:30.726 --> 00:32.858
[light dramatic music]

00:32.902 --> 00:34.991
♪♪

02:19.182 --> 02:20.966
[doorknob clicks]

02:21.010 --> 02:23.230
[door buzzer sounding]

02:25.971 --> 02:27.103
- Oh, they, uh,

02:27.147 --> 02:28.713
they put that system in
a few years ago

02:28.757 --> 02:30.237
after a break-in.

02:32.543 --> 02:33.501
Oh, don't worry.

02:33.544 --> 02:35.242
Neighborhood's a lot
safer now.

02:38.375 --> 02:40.551
[birds chirping]

02:42.945 --> 02:45.382
[wind chimes sounding]

02:49.995 --> 02:51.823
[gate door closing]

02:58.743 --> 03:00.441
- Enchantée!

03:00.963 --> 03:02.443
Enchantée.

03:04.662 --> 03:05.968
- Are you okay?

03:06.447 --> 03:07.796
- Oh.

03:07.839 --> 03:09.580
- Are you alright,
Miss Stanhope?

03:09.798 --> 03:11.278
- Thank you, I'm fine,
I'm fine.

03:11.321 --> 03:13.976
I just--
just a little wobbly.

03:14.455 --> 03:16.413
Thank you, my dear.

03:16.457 --> 03:18.067
Too kind.

03:18.110 --> 03:19.590
- Of course.

03:25.596 --> 03:27.859
[crowd conversing]

03:32.777 --> 03:34.518
- We're not first-come,
first-serve.

03:35.302 --> 03:36.825
Doesn't hurt
to take a look.

03:39.262 --> 03:41.090
I'm Jerry.
I'm the manager.

03:41.133 --> 03:43.788
Just give a shout
if you have a question.

03:46.400 --> 03:48.097
- Are there a lot of dogs
in the building?

03:48.140 --> 03:50.926
- Yeah, it's a pet-free,
smoke-free complex.

04:09.988 --> 04:11.468
Alrighty.

04:11.860 --> 04:13.470
Local contact?

04:13.514 --> 04:16.430
- Yeah, I just moved here.
I don't really know anyone.

04:16.473 --> 04:18.257
- Okay, that's no problem.

04:18.779 --> 04:20.521
What brought you to LA?

04:21.435 --> 04:24.873
- I guess I'm trying
to start a new life.

04:25.352 --> 04:27.092
That sounds ridiculous.
I don't know.

04:27.136 --> 04:29.094
- No, not at all.

04:29.138 --> 04:30.835
It's a good city for that.

04:31.532 --> 04:34.056
Oh, you, uh,
missed one here.

04:34.099 --> 04:35.405
Any pets?

04:36.363 --> 04:37.712
- No.

04:38.278 --> 04:39.670
- Okay.

04:46.982 --> 04:48.810
[cat purring]

04:49.419 --> 04:51.465
- Very helpful, Giles.

04:51.508 --> 04:52.596
Mm.

04:52.640 --> 04:54.772
[cat purring]

04:56.470 --> 04:58.036
Okay.

04:59.647 --> 05:01.953
[cellphone vibrating]

05:07.089 --> 05:08.046
- Hi.

05:08.090 --> 05:09.178
[on phone]
- There you are.

05:09.221 --> 05:11.093
Haven't you been
getting my calls?

05:11.136 --> 05:12.573
- I've been busy.

05:12.964 --> 05:14.357
- When are you
coming home?

05:14.401 --> 05:15.880
[on phone]
- I'm staying.

05:15.924 --> 05:17.099
I got a job.

05:17.142 --> 05:18.361
[on phone]
- Making costumes?

05:18.405 --> 05:20.145
Already?

05:20.189 --> 05:21.886
- No, Dad, I'm--

05:21.930 --> 05:23.584
I'm working as a temp.

05:24.672 --> 05:26.456
At a law firm.
It's just for now.

05:26.500 --> 05:28.980
[on phone]
I'm gonna start taking extension classes next quarter.

05:29.024 --> 05:30.547
- You know, I don't know if
you're trying to punish me

05:30.591 --> 05:32.462
or punish Diane.

05:32.506 --> 05:35.552
But your mother certainly
would not have wanted you--
- Don't.

05:35.596 --> 05:37.554
Dad, please don't.

05:39.469 --> 05:41.384
- I just worry about you,
sweetie.

05:41.428 --> 05:44.431
Do you really think you can
do this all by yourself?

05:46.128 --> 05:48.348
- I don't know.
I guess I'll find out.

05:48.391 --> 05:49.610
[on phone]
- Well, dammit, I'm--

05:49.653 --> 05:50.480
Come on, you know
I didn't mean that--

05:50.524 --> 05:51.612
- Dad, I have to go.

05:51.655 --> 05:53.483
I'll talk to you later,
okay? Bye.

05:55.180 --> 05:57.618
[distant police siren]

06:03.493 --> 06:04.755
[cat meowing]

06:05.190 --> 06:07.454
[keyboard clicking]

06:09.630 --> 06:10.935
- Lisa.

06:11.458 --> 06:13.373
Lisa, I asked you
to renumber the footnotes

06:13.416 --> 06:14.983
for each section.

06:15.026 --> 06:16.158
- No, you didn't.

06:16.201 --> 06:18.203
- Are you calling me a liar?

06:18.247 --> 06:19.466
- You want me
to renumber them?

06:19.509 --> 06:20.728
Just ask.

06:20.771 --> 06:22.860
You don't have to pretend
I fucked up.

06:22.904 --> 06:24.775
Give me half an hour.

06:25.254 --> 06:26.603
Oh, and I'm leaving
at three.

06:26.647 --> 06:28.083
I'm up for a sitcom.

06:30.128 --> 06:31.608
Enjoy the show?

06:31.652 --> 06:32.957
- Sorry.

06:33.001 --> 06:35.438
- Sweetie,
I'm just fucking with you.

06:35.482 --> 06:36.700
I'm Lisa.

06:36.744 --> 06:38.267
You the new temp?

06:38.310 --> 06:40.443
- Sarah.
- Good to meet you.

06:40.487 --> 06:42.010
I'll introduce you
around later.

06:42.053 --> 06:42.967
[whispers]
I know everyone.

06:43.011 --> 06:44.534
[laughs]
- Thanks.

06:44.578 --> 06:46.841
[cellphone vibrating]

06:50.105 --> 06:51.411
Hello?

06:52.586 --> 06:54.283
Yes, this is she.

06:56.764 --> 06:58.330
Really?

07:01.812 --> 07:03.945
[light piano music]

07:03.988 --> 07:06.077
♪♪

07:06.426 --> 07:08.602
[cat meowing]
Shut up, okay?

07:08.645 --> 07:10.473
We're almost there.

07:16.784 --> 07:18.002
[door closing]
- Hey!

07:18.046 --> 07:19.656
You got it!
We're neighbors.

07:19.700 --> 07:21.179
Oh, I'm--
I'm Brian.

07:21.223 --> 07:22.659
- I'm Sarah.
Um...

07:22.703 --> 07:24.444
- Let's do an elbow bump.

07:24.487 --> 07:25.923
[laughs]
- Good to meet you.
- Good to meet you.

07:25.967 --> 07:27.708
Um, hey listen,
we're having a barbecue.

07:27.751 --> 07:28.448
You should come.

07:28.491 --> 07:29.666
- Yeah, I'll try.

07:29.710 --> 07:31.494
Um, I got a bunch
of stuff to bring in.

07:32.756 --> 07:34.105
- Hang on.

07:34.149 --> 07:35.411
Hey, guys,

07:35.455 --> 07:36.499
you wanna give us a hand?
- Yeah, sure!

07:36.543 --> 07:37.718
- Um, yeah,
let me just run-- I'll--

07:37.761 --> 07:39.546
Give me a second, okay?

07:39.676 --> 07:40.851
- Okay.

07:45.073 --> 07:47.684
- How lovely our barbecue

07:47.728 --> 07:51.688
has turned out to be
a welcome party for you.

07:52.733 --> 07:54.299
Enchantée.

07:56.476 --> 07:59.304
Here they are.
Our power couple.

07:59.348 --> 08:00.436
[couple laughing]

08:00.480 --> 08:02.960
Oliver is a big-time attorney,

08:03.004 --> 08:06.921
and Esther is an even
bigger-time doctor.

08:06.964 --> 08:08.575
This is Jessica.

08:08.618 --> 08:11.055
She just moved in
on the second floor.

08:11.099 --> 08:12.274
- Sarah.

08:12.317 --> 08:13.710
- Oh.

08:13.754 --> 08:16.365
I'm sorry, Sarah.
I just--

08:16.408 --> 08:18.280
- No, I'm terrible
with names, too.

08:18.323 --> 08:19.368
It's nice
to meet you both.

08:19.411 --> 08:20.630
- Welcome.

08:20.674 --> 08:22.545
We're so glad to have
you in the building.

08:25.026 --> 08:26.375
- Gettin' settled in okay?

08:26.418 --> 08:28.116
Sure you don't need anything?
- Leave her alone.

08:28.159 --> 08:29.552
She doesn't need us
pestering her.

08:29.596 --> 08:30.640
- Sorry.

08:30.684 --> 08:31.728
We'll stay out
of your hair.

08:31.772 --> 08:32.816
- Oh, no, it's okay.

08:32.860 --> 08:34.339
Everyone's been really nice.

08:34.383 --> 08:35.905
- Good. Good.

08:35.950 --> 08:37.299
We like to make this place
feel like a real neighborhood.

08:37.342 --> 08:38.605
- Mm.
- It's great.

08:38.648 --> 08:40.083
- Yeah, it seems like
most places these days,

08:40.128 --> 08:42.347
people don't even bother
to learn each other's names.

08:42.390 --> 08:45.786
- Oh, speaking of which,
our daughter Natalie--

08:45.829 --> 08:46.874
Natalie!

08:47.091 --> 08:48.179
Natalie!

08:48.223 --> 08:49.659
I saw that.

08:49.703 --> 08:51.356
What's the first rule?

08:53.533 --> 08:54.838
- Sorry.

08:56.318 --> 08:58.494
- [exhales]
- Kids.

08:58.538 --> 08:59.756
Medium rare?

09:05.545 --> 09:07.024
- You should read this.

09:07.068 --> 09:08.330
- I-- what?

09:08.373 --> 09:10.288
- It changed my life.

09:11.333 --> 09:13.596
- Oh, um.
That's okay.

09:13.640 --> 09:15.598
Thanks.

09:25.086 --> 09:26.130
- Hey.

09:26.174 --> 09:27.479
Did you have a good time?

09:27.523 --> 09:28.785
- Yeah.

09:28.829 --> 09:30.178
I still can't believe
I got it.

09:30.221 --> 09:31.919
Out of all those people.

09:33.311 --> 09:34.617
What?

09:34.965 --> 09:37.751
- I might have, uh, put in
a good word with Jerry.

09:39.274 --> 09:42.190
All I did is tell him what
you did for Miss Stanhope.

09:44.018 --> 09:45.367
- Does she have family?

09:45.410 --> 09:46.629
- Just us.

09:46.673 --> 09:49.066
We all kind of take care
of each other here.

09:49.763 --> 09:51.242
- I love that.

09:51.286 --> 09:53.201
LA can be so...

09:54.332 --> 09:56.030
- Lonely.

10:02.427 --> 10:04.821
- I should go.
Unpacking.

10:04.865 --> 10:05.822
- Of course.

10:05.866 --> 10:08.259
Well, um,
goodnight, neighbor.

10:08.869 --> 10:10.435
- Goodnight, neighbor.

10:14.962 --> 10:16.485
Miss Stanhope?

10:16.528 --> 10:18.443
Can I walk you home?
- Oh.

10:18.487 --> 10:21.664
Well, only if
you'll call me Edie.

10:21.708 --> 10:23.666
We're friends, aren't we?

10:25.755 --> 10:27.670
- This is you?

10:27.714 --> 10:29.150
You're beautiful.

10:29.672 --> 10:31.718
Di-- did you see it?

10:33.502 --> 10:35.896
It was a terrible picture.

10:37.027 --> 10:39.377
I was an awful actress.

10:42.337 --> 10:45.253
I'm so much happier now.

10:46.689 --> 10:49.431
I have such wonderful
neighbors.

10:49.474 --> 10:51.476
- You and me both.

11:01.573 --> 11:04.185
[distant indistinct
conversation]

11:52.624 --> 11:55.889
[distant indistinct
conversation]

12:03.026 --> 12:05.420
[distant gate banging]

12:14.342 --> 12:16.910
[plumbing rattles]
[gasps]

12:32.142 --> 12:34.754
[pipes rattling]
[water whirring]

12:38.845 --> 12:40.107
Zoloft.

12:40.150 --> 12:41.761
Fifty milligrams.

12:42.849 --> 12:44.894
Well, when can
I get a refill?

12:46.113 --> 12:47.723
Okay, thanks.

12:47.767 --> 12:49.594
- Hey, I got it,
I got it, I got it.

12:49.638 --> 12:51.596
- Oh, no, you don't--
you don't have to--

12:51.640 --> 12:53.598
- Moving is exhausting.

12:53.642 --> 12:54.991
- Yeah, I didn't sleep well.

12:55.035 --> 12:56.210
- Oh, yeah?

12:56.253 --> 12:57.689
- Does the plumbing
do that every night?

12:57.733 --> 12:58.952
- Do what?

12:58.995 --> 13:00.170
Do you wanna
open the door?

13:00.214 --> 13:02.738
- Oh, no. No.
I-- I got from here.

13:02.782 --> 13:04.522
Thanks.
- You-- you sure?

13:04.914 --> 13:06.263
Um, uh, okay.

13:06.307 --> 13:08.004
Um, I'm just down the hall.

13:10.920 --> 13:12.269
[sighs]

13:12.313 --> 13:14.794
- Giles, you are really
messing with my love life.

13:16.143 --> 13:17.666
Stupid cat.

13:23.890 --> 13:26.631
[plumbing pipes rattle]

13:39.731 --> 13:41.211
[sighs]

13:52.092 --> 13:53.789
Giles?

13:55.878 --> 13:58.315
Giles, come on, buddy.
I need cuddles.

14:03.668 --> 14:05.409
Giles?

14:11.372 --> 14:13.113
[exhales]

14:15.332 --> 14:17.900
[plumbing rattling]

14:37.006 --> 14:38.616
[gasps]

14:52.587 --> 14:54.894
[footsteps approaching]

14:55.285 --> 14:56.504
Edie!

14:57.113 --> 14:58.593
Edie?

15:04.991 --> 15:06.949
Edie, what are you doing?

15:07.645 --> 15:10.953
- I-- I'm okay.

15:11.388 --> 15:12.694
[exhales]

15:13.303 --> 15:15.523
[exhales]
- Thank you.

15:18.134 --> 15:20.136
[pill box clicking]

15:21.442 --> 15:22.660
- I'll refill this every week

15:22.704 --> 15:24.662
so you don't have
to worry about it.

15:24.706 --> 15:26.882
- Are you sure
you don't mind?

15:26.926 --> 15:27.970
- I'm an expert.

15:28.014 --> 15:30.364
I used to do this
for my mom.

15:30.407 --> 15:33.062
Where can I put these so
you'll remember to take them?

15:33.106 --> 15:35.847
- Oh, just put 'em up
on the counter.

15:42.942 --> 15:44.987
- Did that guy
give you this?

15:45.031 --> 15:46.162
- Hmm?

15:46.206 --> 15:47.816
What guy?

15:48.556 --> 15:50.732
- That creepy guy
with the weird glasses.

15:50.775 --> 15:52.864
You know, he tried to
give me this at the party.

15:52.908 --> 15:54.910
- Oh, you mean Lester.

15:54.954 --> 15:59.697
Oh, he's not creepy,
he's just a little bit sad.

15:59.741 --> 16:03.745
He recently lost
his wife to cancer.

16:03.788 --> 16:06.052
Just lovely, lovely lady.

16:06.095 --> 16:08.445
- I'm sorry.
I didn't know.

16:08.489 --> 16:10.230
I didn't mean to--

16:11.144 --> 16:13.146
I'm just tired is all.

16:13.189 --> 16:16.018
Do you hear that noise
that the pipes make at night?

16:16.062 --> 16:20.936
- Oh, honey, I don't hear
anything very well anymore.

16:20.980 --> 16:22.938
[laughs]

16:25.985 --> 16:28.552
[pipes rattling]

16:37.822 --> 16:40.477
- Oh, you've gotta
be fucking kidding me.

16:41.783 --> 16:43.176
[sighs]

16:43.219 --> 16:45.613
[rattling intensifies]

16:50.574 --> 16:51.749
[grunts]

16:54.665 --> 16:56.798
[groans in pain]

17:00.106 --> 17:01.542
[on phone message]
- Sarah, it's Dad.

17:01.585 --> 17:03.674
Give me a call back
when you get this.

17:03.718 --> 17:05.154
Listen, I'm glad
you found a place.

17:05.198 --> 17:07.374
I'm concerned, you don't
seem to have much of a plan

17:07.416 --> 17:10.420
beyond these
extension classes.

17:10.464 --> 17:11.856
Alright, listen,
I'm gonna find time,

17:11.900 --> 17:13.249
I'll fly out--

17:13.292 --> 17:15.077
[cat meows]

17:28.221 --> 17:30.223
[eerie music builds]

17:30.266 --> 17:32.660
♪♪

17:44.280 --> 17:46.804
♪♪

18:08.087 --> 18:09.175
- Hey.

18:10.872 --> 18:12.482
Hey!

18:16.486 --> 18:17.966
[door closes]
- Hey!

18:18.009 --> 18:19.750
I'm, uh,
glad I caught you.

18:21.448 --> 18:22.623
You okay?

18:22.666 --> 18:24.668
- Just tired.
Uh, what's up?

18:24.712 --> 18:27.410
- Um, I'm having a dinner party
later tonight around seven.

18:27.454 --> 18:29.064
Uh, you wanna join us?

18:29.847 --> 18:32.154
- I... I don't know.

18:32.198 --> 18:36.245
- Oh. Um, o-o-okay.
Uh, no pressure.

18:36.289 --> 18:38.378
I-- it was,
uh, short notice.

18:38.421 --> 18:40.728
- No, it sounds--
it sounds really great.

18:40.771 --> 18:42.512
I'll be there.
- Yeah?

18:42.556 --> 18:43.731
Well, alright.

18:43.774 --> 18:45.254
Then I'll see you
tonight then, neighbor.

18:49.258 --> 18:51.956
[distant phone ringing]

18:54.959 --> 18:56.135
[mouse clicking]

18:56.178 --> 18:57.832
- Sarah.
Check your e-mail.

18:57.875 --> 18:59.834
I got two more reports
from accounting.

18:59.877 --> 19:01.792
- Uh, could I do them
first thing in the morning?

19:01.836 --> 19:03.098
I just--
- No, today.

19:03.142 --> 19:04.404
But, clock out first.

19:04.447 --> 19:06.406
We can't pay
overtime on this.

19:07.233 --> 19:08.843
Mm-kay?

19:10.671 --> 19:12.151
- Sure.

19:18.113 --> 19:19.636
- Hey.

19:19.984 --> 19:21.421
Hey.

19:22.422 --> 19:24.293
Fuck that
hatchet-faced bitch.

19:24.337 --> 19:25.468
- [laughs]

19:26.643 --> 19:29.037
I don't know why
I can't just--

19:29.080 --> 19:30.952
God, I'm so tired.

19:30.995 --> 19:33.346
- You do look like dog shit.

19:34.260 --> 19:36.175
[laughs]
- Thanks.

19:36.566 --> 19:38.264
It's my fucking apartment.

19:38.307 --> 19:39.700
- I thought you
loved that place.

19:39.743 --> 19:41.441
Hot neighbor guy?

19:46.272 --> 19:48.099
You like Thai food?

19:49.623 --> 19:51.364
- Yeah, I--

19:51.407 --> 19:52.756
Oh, shit.

19:52.800 --> 19:54.758
I was supposed
to go to this.

19:56.282 --> 19:58.197
- Doesn't matter.
It's fine.

19:59.720 --> 20:01.112
- There you are.

20:01.156 --> 20:02.549
- Hey.

20:02.592 --> 20:03.593
I'm sorry.

20:03.637 --> 20:06.074
I forgot I already
had other plans.

20:06.117 --> 20:07.031
- Oh.

20:07.075 --> 20:08.685
Uh, don't worry about it.

20:08.729 --> 20:10.470
Uh, we're gonna be having
dessert a little later

20:10.513 --> 20:12.254
if you wanna stop by.

20:12.298 --> 20:13.995
- Yeah.
Maybe.

20:14.909 --> 20:16.302
- Okay.

20:19.087 --> 20:20.871
- Is that the guy?

20:20.915 --> 20:22.743
[chuckles]
He's cute.

20:24.179 --> 20:25.659
[whispers]
- Oh, Giles.

20:25.789 --> 20:27.443
That's disgusting.

20:37.323 --> 20:39.586
You think I'm crazy.
- No.

20:40.630 --> 20:42.023
[chuckles]
I don't know.

20:42.066 --> 20:42.937
Maybe?

20:42.980 --> 20:44.243
It looks kinda great.

20:44.286 --> 20:45.722
- No, I know.

20:47.420 --> 20:48.421
It's just normally
the pipes would be--
- Did you do these?

20:48.464 --> 20:49.987
They're really good.

20:50.031 --> 20:51.206
- Oh, shit.

20:51.250 --> 20:52.642
- What?

20:52.686 --> 20:54.340
I was supposed to--

20:54.383 --> 20:55.819
God, I completely forgot.

20:55.863 --> 20:59.083
I-- I missed the deadline
for the extension program.

20:59.127 --> 21:01.564
I'm so fucking tired
all the time,

21:01.608 --> 21:03.262
and I can't get
my prescription,

21:03.305 --> 21:05.264
and I keep getting
these headaches, and--

21:05.307 --> 21:06.830
and my neighbor is
gonna report my cat,

21:06.874 --> 21:08.484
so then I'll have
no one left to talk to.

21:08.528 --> 21:10.791
- Hey, it's okay.

21:10.834 --> 21:12.358
You can always pet my head.

21:12.401 --> 21:14.185
[laughs]

21:15.709 --> 21:17.319
Maybe fucking asshole
Dad is right,

21:17.363 --> 21:18.929
and I should just go home.

21:18.973 --> 21:20.104
- No.

21:20.148 --> 21:21.323
That's some horseshit.

21:21.367 --> 21:22.368
- I don't know.

21:22.411 --> 21:24.631
I was always
such a daddy's girl.

21:24.674 --> 21:26.197
You would've hated me.

