48:49.622 --> 48:51.102
What happened
between you two?

48:51.145 --> 48:53.365
You never talked or e-mailed
anybody about it.

48:53.408 --> 48:55.323
Least not
that we could find.

48:59.371 --> 49:00.981
I caught him cheating
on my mother

49:01.025 --> 49:02.765
while she was dying.

49:03.505 --> 49:05.551
- Yes, we inferred that.

49:05.594 --> 49:07.248
- With her nurse.

49:09.555 --> 49:12.297
I said I'd tell her
if they didn't stop.

49:12.427 --> 49:13.733
- And did they?

49:16.344 --> 49:18.303
- He knew I couldn't do it.

49:20.566 --> 49:22.785
She was already so weak,
it would've--

49:24.396 --> 49:26.398
[sighs]

49:27.965 --> 49:30.532
She died thinking
he was a saint.

49:34.406 --> 49:39.324
- Sarah, do you want to be
a part of this community?

49:43.110 --> 49:44.720
- Yes.

49:46.461 --> 49:48.202
- Sarah.

49:48.246 --> 49:49.595
- No.

49:49.638 --> 49:51.858
No, I'm sorry, Jerry.
I want to want it.

49:51.901 --> 49:52.946
I-- I'm trying.

49:52.990 --> 49:54.034
I promise.
Please, pl--

49:54.078 --> 49:56.428
- It's alright.
You'll get there.

49:58.691 --> 50:00.171
Let's move on.

50:02.869 --> 50:04.914
[eerie music]

50:04.958 --> 50:07.004
♪♪

50:10.442 --> 50:12.618
[locks clicking]
[door creaks open]

50:14.837 --> 50:16.578
[on monitor]
- It's time to start
contributing.

50:38.122 --> 50:39.732
This way.

50:44.911 --> 50:47.044
[on video]
- Modern society is sick.

50:48.480 --> 50:52.484
Greed, envy,
dishonesty, lust.

50:54.138 --> 50:58.229
The vices that corrode society
all spring from one source.

50:58.272 --> 51:00.448
Selfishness.

51:00.492 --> 51:03.060
- Well, isn't that just
human nature?

51:03.103 --> 51:04.800
- Of course it is.

51:04.844 --> 51:07.629
But we have the technology
to change our nature.

51:07.673 --> 51:09.631
We-- we've had it
for decades.

51:09.675 --> 51:12.721
Thorndike, Watson,
Pavlov, Skinner.

51:12.765 --> 51:15.246
All we've lacked
is an understanding

51:15.289 --> 51:17.074
of what to change to.

51:17.900 --> 51:19.250
Until now.

51:19.293 --> 51:20.468
- Okay.

51:20.512 --> 51:22.949
Uh, let's say I wanna
become this new,

51:22.992 --> 51:24.298
improved human.

51:24.342 --> 51:25.430
What do I do?

51:25.473 --> 51:26.909
- [chuckles]

51:27.649 --> 51:29.651
You live by
four foundations.

51:30.870 --> 51:35.918
First, and most importantly,
selflessness.

51:35.962 --> 51:38.965
You always act in the best
interest of the community.

51:39.183 --> 51:40.967
[dramatic piano music]

51:41.010 --> 51:42.795
♪♪

51:44.362 --> 51:47.104
- Second, openness.

51:48.888 --> 51:51.020
Secrets breed discord.

51:57.984 --> 52:00.726
Third, acceptance.

52:15.001 --> 52:17.046
Once an error
has been corrected...

52:21.921 --> 52:23.879
it's already forgiven.

52:25.229 --> 52:27.187
[piano music continues]

52:27.231 --> 52:29.146
♪♪

52:31.496 --> 52:34.238
Finally, security.

52:34.760 --> 52:35.935
We're our best selves

52:35.978 --> 52:37.719
when we know our
neighbors are watching.

52:39.199 --> 52:41.419
♪♪

52:47.120 --> 52:48.339
- Well, fine,

52:48.382 --> 52:50.210
but how is
the ordinary Joe

52:50.254 --> 52:53.082
supposed to become
this perfect citizen?

52:53.474 --> 52:55.389
- It's not unlike childhood.

52:55.433 --> 52:57.261
At first,
we only follow the rules

52:57.304 --> 52:59.132
so we don't get spanked.

53:01.439 --> 53:02.875
But soon enough,

53:02.918 --> 53:06.705
living the foundations
becomes a habit.

53:06.748 --> 53:09.011
Then it becomes
who we are.

53:10.187 --> 53:12.406
And when that happens,

53:12.450 --> 53:16.454
we will make of this world
a single, perfect community.

53:17.237 --> 53:19.413
Free of loneliness,

53:19.457 --> 53:21.285
free of poverty,

53:22.024 --> 53:23.765
free of strife.

53:27.943 --> 53:29.771
- Why did you choose me?

53:31.991 --> 53:34.472
- Because you needed us.

53:34.515 --> 53:36.735
I could tell
the moment we met.

53:37.562 --> 53:39.999
And, we needed you.

53:40.042 --> 53:42.349
Everybody here
has a role to play.

53:44.786 --> 53:46.832
- What's my role?

53:46.875 --> 53:49.051
- Let's see how far
we've come.

53:51.053 --> 53:53.273
Do you want to be a part
of this community?

53:54.927 --> 53:56.711
- I...

53:59.323 --> 54:01.238
I don't know.

54:03.414 --> 54:04.458
- I think you're ready
to take on

54:04.502 --> 54:06.852
a little bit more
responsibility.

54:09.333 --> 54:11.422
[door creaks open]

54:36.055 --> 54:37.665
[door clicks shut]

54:41.234 --> 54:43.192
[mouse clicking]

55:07.695 --> 55:09.349
- Who's watching us?

55:13.135 --> 55:15.224
- That's none
of our business.

55:15.834 --> 55:17.923
Eyes back on your monitor.

55:19.838 --> 55:21.840
- [sighs]

55:27.149 --> 55:28.063
Edie, she's--

55:28.107 --> 55:30.065
- [coughing]
[wheezing]

55:30.109 --> 55:32.198
- Esther.
How-- how do we call Esther?

55:34.287 --> 55:36.333
[phone dialing]

55:38.030 --> 55:39.727
- Mm-hmm.

55:39.771 --> 55:42.121
Yeah, I agree.

55:43.905 --> 55:45.690
Okay, I'll call you back.

55:47.822 --> 55:49.433
I'm proud of you,
Sarah.

55:49.476 --> 55:51.348
What you did for Edie,

55:52.261 --> 55:54.438
that's what this
community's all about.

56:00.487 --> 56:02.359
- Edie, is this comfortable?

56:04.448 --> 56:05.971
Can I get you anything?

56:06.014 --> 56:08.147
- Oh, no, dear.
I'm fine.

56:08.974 --> 56:10.367
- Hi, Edie.

56:10.410 --> 56:11.759
How are you feeling?

56:11.803 --> 56:15.850
- Oh, I'm doing fine.
I'm so glad that you came.

56:15.894 --> 56:17.983
Come on in,
my dears.

56:18.244 --> 56:21.856
It's so good to see you.
Come on in, everybody.

56:21.900 --> 56:22.944
- Um, maybe I should go.

56:22.988 --> 56:24.206
I feel like
I'm in the way here.

56:24.250 --> 56:28.341
- No, I want you
by my side for this, dear.

56:39.134 --> 56:41.572
- Edie asked me
to say a few words.

56:42.964 --> 56:46.011
When I first arrived here
nine years ago,

56:46.054 --> 56:48.666
Edie was the first person
to introduce herself.

56:48.709 --> 56:51.712
As I know she was
for so many of you.

56:52.191 --> 56:54.759
Of course, back then,
it wasn't Edie,

56:54.802 --> 56:57.457
it was Miss Stanhope
until she told you otherwise.

56:57.501 --> 56:59.503
[all laughing]

57:02.767 --> 57:03.942
Edie,

57:05.465 --> 57:08.250
you have been an essential
member of this community

57:08.294 --> 57:10.514
for longer than most
of us have been here.

57:11.428 --> 57:14.866
You have been a great friend,
and mother,

57:14.909 --> 57:16.868
to all of us.

57:21.525 --> 57:23.744
And we're gonna miss you.

57:24.876 --> 57:26.355
So much.

57:26.399 --> 57:28.488
- [exhales]

57:31.622 --> 57:33.406
- [exhales]
[sniffs]

57:33.450 --> 57:35.408
- You can't do this.
- [shushes]

57:35.974 --> 57:38.411
She can't contribute
to the community anymore,

57:38.455 --> 57:39.891
and we don't have
the resources

57:39.934 --> 57:40.979
to take care of her.

57:41.022 --> 57:42.197
- I-- I'll take care of her.
Just me.

57:42.241 --> 57:44.722
- That is not what
you're here for.

57:46.071 --> 57:48.900
She knows this is what's
best for the community.

57:48.943 --> 57:50.467
- [gasps]

57:51.076 --> 57:53.470
- Don't ruin this.

57:56.081 --> 57:58.039
[dramatic piano music]

57:58.083 --> 58:00.085
♪♪

58:11.705 --> 58:14.142
- I'm so glad you're here.

58:22.542 --> 58:24.457
Goodbye, my dears.

58:25.153 --> 58:26.198
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

58:26.328 --> 58:27.852
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

58:27.895 --> 58:29.462
- Goodbye, Edie.

58:40.647 --> 58:43.128
[gas hissing]

58:44.521 --> 58:47.611
- [breathes heavily]

59:04.802 --> 59:06.804
[dramatic music builds]

59:06.847 --> 59:09.284
♪♪

59:19.904 --> 59:23.081
- When I got back from Iraq,
I was a mess.

59:26.432 --> 59:28.521
At first,
I thought it was hell.

59:31.742 --> 59:35.789
It took me years,
but I finally understood.

59:36.877 --> 59:39.053
They saved my life.

59:43.101 --> 59:45.973
When you let go
and embrace this community

59:46.017 --> 59:47.932
with all your heart,

59:48.454 --> 59:51.457
there is nothing we won't do
to make you happy.

59:56.418 --> 59:59.204
- You probably know
what I'm gonna ask next.

01:00:02.294 --> 01:00:06.167
Sarah, do you want to be
a part of this community?

01:00:09.257 --> 01:00:10.998
- Yes.

01:00:14.567 --> 01:00:16.874
[upbeat guitar music]

01:00:16.917 --> 01:00:18.963
♪♪

01:00:25.796 --> 01:00:29.321
♪ There'll be no strings
to bind your hands

01:00:29.364 --> 01:00:33.107
♪ Not if my love
can't bind your heart

01:00:36.284 --> 01:00:37.677
Kneel.

01:00:37.721 --> 01:00:41.376
♪ And there's no need
to take a stand

01:00:41.420 --> 01:00:45.032
♪ For it was I
who chose to start

01:00:49.863 --> 01:00:54.259
♪ I see no reason
to take me home

01:00:54.302 --> 01:00:55.695
[torch hissing]

01:00:55.739 --> 01:00:59.394
♪ I'm old enough
to face the dawn

01:01:01.701 --> 01:01:06.663
♪ Just call me angel
of the morning, angel

01:01:06.706 --> 01:01:08.229
[all cheering]

01:01:08.273 --> 01:01:13.191
♪ Just touch my cheek
before you leave me, baby

01:01:13.495 --> 01:01:17.064
♪ Just call me angel
of the morning, angel

01:01:17.108 --> 01:01:18.718
- I knew you'd make it.

01:01:26.857 --> 01:01:28.423
[all]
- Aw.

01:01:28.467 --> 01:01:30.077
- Welcome
to the community.

01:01:30.730 --> 01:01:32.906
- Thank you.
- [laughs]

01:01:32.950 --> 01:01:35.735
I told you you'd
thank me one day.

01:01:35.779 --> 01:01:37.171
[laughs]

01:01:37.215 --> 01:01:39.043
Come on,
let's party!

01:01:39.086 --> 01:01:40.697
[all]
- Yeah!

01:01:40.740 --> 01:01:42.699
- [all cheering]
- Come on!

01:01:43.656 --> 01:01:45.049
♪ Just call me angel ♪

01:01:48.530 --> 01:01:50.358
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

01:01:50.402 --> 01:01:51.751
- We're so happy you're here.

01:01:51.795 --> 01:01:53.361
It's just wonderful.

01:01:53.405 --> 01:01:55.059
[laughs]

01:01:56.538 --> 01:01:57.714
- Everybody,

01:01:57.757 --> 01:01:59.324
can I have your attention?

01:02:00.412 --> 01:02:02.762
Sarah, I know you've
been anxious to know

01:02:02.806 --> 01:02:04.851
how you're gonna
fit in here.

01:02:04.895 --> 01:02:07.071
Six months ago,
we lost a beloved member

01:02:07.114 --> 01:02:09.160
of our community to cancer.

01:02:09.987 --> 01:02:11.466
You never got
to know Jessica,

01:02:11.510 --> 01:02:14.295
but the minute Lester saw you,
he said to me

01:02:14.339 --> 01:02:15.906
that you seemed, uh...

01:02:16.820 --> 01:02:18.386
How'd you put it?

01:02:18.430 --> 01:02:22.042
"S-- smart and kind
like my Jessie."

01:02:23.696 --> 01:02:25.654
Come here, you two.
Come on.

01:02:27.178 --> 01:02:28.745
Come on.

01:02:37.841 --> 01:02:39.277
Sarah,

01:02:39.320 --> 01:02:43.107
Lester is as selfless a person
as I have ever known.

01:02:43.150 --> 01:02:45.196
He's gonna take
good care of you.

01:02:47.546 --> 01:02:49.243
And Lester,

01:02:49.287 --> 01:02:52.203
I know how hard it's been
on you losing Jessica.

01:02:52.246 --> 01:02:55.989
But we all saw how devoted
Sarah was to Edie.

01:02:56.033 --> 01:02:59.863
She's a perfect fit
for the community

01:02:59.906 --> 01:03:01.603
and for you.

01:03:02.213 --> 01:03:04.563
Y'all are gonna make
a great couple.

01:03:06.217 --> 01:03:08.175
Great parents.

01:03:09.829 --> 01:03:13.180
Well, go on.

01:03:13.224 --> 01:03:14.878
Come on.

01:03:22.886 --> 01:03:25.758
[all cheering]

01:03:27.151 --> 01:03:28.674
[whispering]
- Let's go home.

01:03:45.909 --> 01:03:47.867
- What-- what about
my apartment?

01:03:47.911 --> 01:03:49.390
- It's not your apartment.

01:03:49.434 --> 01:03:51.262
It's for new candidates.

01:03:51.305 --> 01:03:52.829
Come here.

01:03:57.790 --> 01:04:00.097
[dramatic music]

01:04:00.140 --> 01:04:02.447
♪♪

01:04:07.191 --> 01:04:09.019
Come here.

01:04:09.758 --> 01:04:11.891
[rapid footsteps approach]

01:04:13.850 --> 01:04:15.199
Sarah.

01:04:15.242 --> 01:04:16.809
We have a problem.

01:04:27.080 --> 01:04:28.865
Fourth foundation.

01:04:30.214 --> 01:04:31.998
You know what
has to happen.

01:04:32.042 --> 01:04:34.348
[cellphone vibrating]

01:04:34.740 --> 01:04:37.525
Unless you can make him leave
and never come back.

01:04:40.877 --> 01:04:42.443
[on phone]
- Sarah, I need
to talk to you.

01:04:42.487 --> 01:04:43.662
[on phone]
- I'm at work.

01:04:43.705 --> 01:04:44.968
[phone disconnects]
Come back at six.

01:04:47.535 --> 01:04:49.668
[dramatic music]

01:04:49.711 --> 01:04:52.062
♪♪

01:05:01.332 --> 01:05:02.855
[door closes]

01:05:11.733 --> 01:05:13.257
- Sarah.

01:05:16.173 --> 01:05:17.696
He's here.

01:05:22.788 --> 01:05:24.442
[knocking on door]

01:05:28.054 --> 01:05:29.926
[knocking continues]

01:05:38.064 --> 01:05:39.631
- Sarah, you--

01:05:40.284 --> 01:05:42.068
What happened to you?

01:05:43.635 --> 01:05:45.158
Are you alright?

01:05:45.593 --> 01:05:47.247
- I'm fine.

01:05:47.291 --> 01:05:48.814
What do you want?

01:05:50.511 --> 01:05:52.078
- I know, y-y-you
don't want to see me,

01:05:52.122 --> 01:05:53.558
but I-- [sighs]

01:05:53.601 --> 01:05:54.994
Oh, dammit,

01:05:55.038 --> 01:05:57.431
I don't want things
to be like this between us.

01:05:57.475 --> 01:05:59.085
- You think I care
what you want?

01:05:59.129 --> 01:06:00.304
- [laughs]

01:06:00.347 --> 01:06:02.045
- They're right,
you're such a narcissist.

01:06:02.088 --> 01:06:04.134
- Who-who-who--
- You're just so sure
this is all about you.

01:06:06.005 --> 01:06:07.180
- You're right.

01:06:07.224 --> 01:06:09.095
I've been doing
a lot of thinking.

01:06:09.139 --> 01:06:11.054
I wanna be a better father.

01:06:12.316 --> 01:06:13.491
- Fuck you.

01:06:13.534 --> 01:06:15.623
You're a little
fucking late.

01:06:15.667 --> 01:06:17.016
I've wasted my whole life

01:06:17.060 --> 01:06:18.583
trying to be who
you wanted me to be.

01:06:18.626 --> 01:06:20.367
Well, not anymore.

01:06:20.411 --> 01:06:22.630
I have a real family now.

01:06:22.674 --> 01:06:24.589
Go back to Diane.

01:06:24.632 --> 01:06:27.113
- Honey, I flew across the--
- Go!

01:06:27.157 --> 01:06:29.768
I don't ever want
to see you again.

01:06:42.433 --> 01:06:44.261
[door opens]

01:06:46.219 --> 01:06:48.134
- Sarah.

01:06:48.178 --> 01:06:49.875
I'm sorry.

01:06:51.355 --> 01:06:53.444
I screwed up.
I know.

01:06:54.314 --> 01:06:56.708
I never should've put you
in that spot with Mom.

01:06:57.839 --> 01:06:59.972
I should have
been there for her.

01:07:01.582 --> 01:07:03.236
And for you.

01:07:03.280 --> 01:07:04.585
I...

01:07:06.326 --> 01:07:08.198
and I will.

01:07:08.241 --> 01:07:10.026
I promise.

01:07:10.635 --> 01:07:12.376
Whatever you want,
whatever your dreams are,

01:07:12.419 --> 01:07:15.335
I-- I'm so proud of you.

01:07:16.554 --> 01:07:17.990
Sarah?

01:07:18.034 --> 01:07:20.036
Can you forgive me?

01:07:21.994 --> 01:07:24.170
I can't lose you, too.

01:07:24.214 --> 01:07:26.433
- [cries]

01:07:31.482 --> 01:07:33.310
[crying]
- I love you.

01:07:38.706 --> 01:07:40.360
- No! [gasps]
- What?

01:07:41.318 --> 01:07:42.667
- [inhales]

01:07:42.710 --> 01:07:44.843
You really think Mom
didn't know?

01:07:44.886 --> 01:07:46.366
You think
I wouldn't tell her?

01:07:46.410 --> 01:07:48.412
I told her everything.

01:07:48.455 --> 01:07:51.893
She knew exactly what
a pathetic coward you are.

01:07:51.937 --> 01:07:53.112
- But--

01:07:53.156 --> 01:07:56.594
- She died hating
your disgusting guts.

01:07:58.552 --> 01:08:00.250
[smack]

01:08:04.515 --> 01:08:06.560
Get the fuck out.

01:08:12.827 --> 01:08:14.786
- If I leave,
I'm never com--

01:08:14.829 --> 01:08:18.354
- The next time I want to
see you is at your funeral.

01:08:32.456 --> 01:08:34.719
[door opens/closes]

01:08:38.939 --> 01:08:40.942
[door buzzer sounding]

01:08:47.122 --> 01:08:48.385
- Okay.

01:08:48.602 --> 01:08:50.037
Got it.

01:08:56.479 --> 01:08:58.395
He's gone.

01:08:59.961 --> 01:09:01.832
You did great.

01:09:03.008 --> 01:09:05.880
- [exhales/crying]
- Hey, hey, hey.

01:09:05.924 --> 01:09:07.143
It's okay.

01:09:07.578 --> 01:09:09.014
It's okay.

01:09:09.841 --> 01:09:11.625
It's okay.
- [crying]

01:09:29.426 --> 01:09:31.515
- We were interrupted
last time.

01:09:47.357 --> 01:09:49.185
[exhales]

01:10:03.242 --> 01:10:05.026
- Thank you.

01:10:07.594 --> 01:10:10.206
- This is strange
for me, too.

01:10:11.816 --> 01:10:13.383
[sighs]

01:10:14.340 --> 01:10:16.690
My first five years,

01:10:16.995 --> 01:10:20.738
all I could think about
was trying to escape.

01:10:21.217 --> 01:10:23.131
Or kill myself.

01:10:24.176 --> 01:10:26.396
Jessie, she saved me.

01:10:26.961 --> 01:10:32.619
She helped me finally
accept that this is my life.

01:10:37.494 --> 01:10:39.365
This is our life.

01:10:40.540 --> 01:10:42.716
Nothing can change that.

01:10:42.760 --> 01:10:44.892
[dramatic piano music]

01:10:44.936 --> 01:10:47.765
♪♪

01:10:48.853 --> 01:10:50.855
But it could be a good life.

01:11:34.551 --> 01:11:37.293
[birds chirping]

01:11:43.211 --> 01:11:46.127
[indistinct conversations]

01:11:51.655 --> 01:11:52.786
- Hey, guys.

01:11:52.830 --> 01:11:53.918
- You're early.

01:11:53.961 --> 01:11:55.833
- Get outta here.
Natty misses you.

